Durban -Residents of the Bottlebrush informal settlement in Chatsworth went on the rampage on Sunday afternoon, stoning cars and burning three boats and tyres.
The protests were sparked after a five-year-old girl  died. She was knocked by a motorist travelling on Link Road.

It is believed the protesters removed the boats forcibly from a nearby resident’s home.














